<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,692,900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,692,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Distribution:</emphasis>
This species was recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[684,780,693,719]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[839,898,693,719]" name="Syria" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Syria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaltenbach, A." box="[914,1112,693,720]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="3 - 107" refId="ref11446" refString="Kaltenbach, A. (1967) Unterlagen fur eine Monographie der Saginae I. Superrevision der Gattung Saga Charpentier (Saltatoria: Tettigoniidae), Beitrage zur Entomologie, 17, 3 - 107." type="journal article" year="1967">Kaltenbach 1967</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution of species in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,276,729,755]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
has intensified mostly in Mediterranean and South-Eastern parts (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1154,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1661,1686]" captionTargetBox="[195,1396,964,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,913,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map (A) and male calling song of Saga beieri (B—phrase series, C—one complete phrase and D—a group of syllables, black arrow is the hypothetic opening hemisyllable movement and grey arrow is the hypothetic closing hemisyllable movement)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3383544/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
) of it (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaltenbach, A." box="[1234,1431,729,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="3 - 107" refId="ref11446" refString="Kaltenbach, A. (1967) Unterlagen fur eine Monographie der Saginae I. Superrevision der Gattung Saga Charpentier (Saltatoria: Tettigoniidae), Beitrage zur Entomologie, 17, 3 - 107." type="journal article" year="1967">Kaltenbach 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Naskrecki, P. &amp; Unal, M." box="[151,422,764,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" pagination="393 - 412" refId="ref12148" refString="Naskrecki, P. &amp; Unal, M. (1995) The Orthoptera of Hatay Province, S. Turkey. Beitrage zur Entomologie, 45, 393 - 412." type="journal article" year="1995">Naskrecki &amp; Ünal 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,692,900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,391,800,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Song recording:</emphasis>
Male specimens are collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[795,876,801,827]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[887,969,801,827]" country="Turkey" name="Mersin" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Mersin</collectingRegion>
, Tarsus, road of Gülek pass, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1291,1432,800,827]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="15.00" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" precision="9" value="37.25">N 37°15.00’</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,304,837,863]" degrees="034" direction="east" minutes="46.29" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" precision="9" value="34.7715">E 034°46.29’</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[316,404,837,863]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0859999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" unit="m" value="1086.0">1086 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[416,555,836,863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" value="2017-07-25">25.VII.2017</date>
, leg.: H. Sevgili, D. Sirin, A. Mol &amp; M.S. Taylan and the calling songs are re- corded from one male at 28 ˚C in the room conditions (by D. Şirin).
</paragraph>
